# Whitelist: deny everything by default, then allow ONLY tracked file types
# and explicitly-tracked hidden files.
#
# Mental model: if a path isn't matched by an allow rule below, it is
# ignored. This includes secrets (.env), build artifacts (__pycache__,
# *.pyc), IDE/OS files (.vscode, .DS_Store), virtualenvs (.venv),
# downloaded media (downloads/), and any future file types we haven't
# deliberately opted in to.

# --- deny all files (hidden + non-hidden) -----------------------------------
.*
*

# --- allow common tracked source/config file types -------------------------
!*.py
!*.yml
!*.yaml
!*.md
!*.sh
!*.html
!*.css
!*.js
!*.svg
!*.png
!*.jpg
!*.jpeg
!*.txt
!*.json
!*.toml
!Dockerfile
!Dockerfile.*

# --- allow all directories (so patterns above can match their contents) ----
!*/

# --- explicit denies for hidden directories the allow rules above would
# otherwise re-introduce. !*/ brings back every directory; these patterns
# (no leading !) re-deny the IDE/tooling directories that should never be
# tracked.
.vscode/
.vscode/**
.idea/
.idea/**

# --- explicit denies (override the allow rules above for known-bad paths) ---
# These files are not tracked and should never be: personal scratch pads,
# local config, generated reports, secrets, runtime data volumes, and the
# build/install artifacts most projects produce.
DESIGN.md
CLAUDE.md
docs/
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
.venv/
downloads/
telegram-bot-api-data/
dashboard-data/
__pycache__/
**/__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
*.pyd
.pytest_cache/
.pytest_cache
.pytest_cache/**
*.log
*.tmp
*.swp
*.swo
.DS_Store

# --- explicitly allow tracked hidden files ---------------------------------
!.gitignore
!.dockerignore
!.env.example